{
  "video_id": "ta2Wvy9F_gA",
  "title": "A climate solution where all sides can win | Ted Halstead",
  "es": 1,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 13185.0,
      "end_time": 15662.0,
      "text": "I have a two-year-old daughter named Naya"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 15686.0,
      "end_time": 17552.0,
      "text": "who is under the mistaken impression"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 17576.0,
      "end_time": 21139.0,
      "text": "that this conference is named in honor of her father."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 21163.0,
      "end_time": 22462.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 22486.0,
      "end_time": 24622.0,
      "text": "Who am I to contradict my baby girl?"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 25495.0,
      "end_time": 29365.0,
      "text": "As many of you know, there&#39;s something about becoming a parent"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 29389.0,
      "end_time": 33849.0,
      "text": "that concentrates the mind on long-term problems like climate change."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 34404.0,
      "end_time": 36869.0,
      "text": "It was the birth of my daughter that inspired me"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 36893.0,
      "end_time": 39447.0,
      "text": "to launch this climate organization,"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 39471.0,
      "end_time": 43342.0,
      "text": "in order to counteract the excessive polarization of this issue"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 43366.0,
      "end_time": 44675.0,
      "text": "in the United States,"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 44699.0,
      "end_time": 49152.0,
      "text": "and to find a conservative pathway forward."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 49970.0,
      "end_time": 54603.0,
      "text": "Yes, folks, a Republican climate solution is possible,"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 54627.0,
      "end_time": 55952.0,
      "text": "and you know what?"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 55976.0,
      "end_time": 58308.0,
      "text": "It may even be better."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 58332.0,
      "end_time": 59943.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 59967.0,
      "end_time": 61628.0,
      "text": "Let me try to prove that to you."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 63890.0,
      "end_time": 67663.0,
      "text": "What we really need is a killer app to climate policy."
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 67687.0,
      "end_time": 72104.0,
      "text": "In the technology world, a killer app is an application so transformative"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 72128.0,
      "end_time": 73607.0,
      "text": "that it creates its own market,"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 73631.0,
      "end_time": 75196.0,
      "text": "like Uber."
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 75220.0,
      "end_time": 76847.0,
      "text": "In the climate world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 76871.0,
      "end_time": 81795.0,
      "text": "a killer app is a new solution so promising"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 81820.0,
      "end_time": 85366.0,
      "text": "that it can break through the seemingly insurmountable"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 85391.0,
      "end_time": 87252.0,
      "text": "barriers to progress."
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 87276.0,
      "end_time": 90801.0,
      "text": "These include the psychological barrier."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 90825.0,
      "end_time": 94380.0,
      "text": "Climate advocates have long been encouraging their fellow citizens"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 94620.0,
      "end_time": 95972.0,
      "text": "to make short-term sacrifices now"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 95996.0,
      "end_time": 98330.0,
      "text": "for benefits that accrue to other people"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 98570.0,
      "end_time": 101401.0,
      "text": "in other countries 30 or 40 years in the future."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 101425.0,
      "end_time": 105728.0,
      "text": "It just doesn&#39;t fly because it runs contrary to basic human nature."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 106507.0,
      "end_time": 109820.0,
      "text": "Next is the geopolitical barrier."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 109844.0,
      "end_time": 112112.0,
      "text": "Under the current rules of global trade,"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 112136.0,
      "end_time": 116482.0,
      "text": "countries have a strong incentive to free ride off the emissions reductions"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 116506.0,
      "end_time": 117765.0,
      "text": "of other nations,"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 117789.0,
      "end_time": 120210.0,
      "text": "instead of strengthening their own programs."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 120450.0,
      "end_time": 121603.0,
      "text": "This has been the curse"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 121627.0,
      "end_time": 125589.0,
      "text": "of every international climate negotiations, including Paris."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 126243.0,
      "end_time": 129298.0,
      "text": "Finally, we have the partisan barrier."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 129322.0,
      "end_time": 131393.0,
      "text": "Even the most committed countries --"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 131417.0,
      "end_time": 134617.0,
      "text": "Germany, the United Kingdom, Canada --"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 134641.0,
      "end_time": 139362.0,
      "text": "are nowhere near reducing emissions at the required scale and speed."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 139386.0,
      "end_time": 140853.0,
      "text": "Not even close."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 140878.0,
      "end_time": 145128.0,
      "text": "And the partisan climate divide is far more acute"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 145152.0,
      "end_time": 147240.0,
      "text": "here in the United States."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 147623.0,
      "end_time": 149728.0,
      "text": "We are fundamentally stuck,"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 149753.0,
      "end_time": 153313.0,
      "text": "and that is why we need a killer app of climate policy"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 153337.0,
      "end_time": 156780.0,
      "text": "to break through each of these barriers."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 156570.0,
      "end_time": 162238.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m convinced that the road to climate progress in the United States"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 162262.0,
      "end_time": 164877.0,
      "text": "runs through the Republican Party"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 164901.0,
      "end_time": 166985.0,
      "text": "and the business community."
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 168720.0,
      "end_time": 170828.0,
      "text": "So in launching the Climate Leadership Council,"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 170852.0,
      "end_time": 174766.0,
      "text": "I started by reaching out to a who&#39;s who of Republican elder statesmen"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 174790.0,
      "end_time": 175980.0,
      "text": "and business leaders,"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 176400.0,
      "end_time": 179381.0,
      "text": "including James Baker and George Schultz,"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 179405.0,
      "end_time": 183525.0,
      "text": "the two most respected Republican elder statesmen in America;"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 183549.0,
      "end_time": 185418.0,
      "text": "Martin Feldstein and Greg Mankiw,"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 185442.0,
      "end_time": 189840.0,
      "text": "the two most respected conservative economists in the country;"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 189108.0,
      "end_time": 191201.0,
      "text": "and Henry Paulson and Rob Walton,"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 191225.0,
      "end_time": 194194.0,
      "text": "two of the most successful and admired business leaders."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 194218.0,
      "end_time": 196518.0,
      "text": "Together, we co-authored"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 196543.0,
      "end_time": 199607.0,
      "text": "\"The Conservative Case For Carbon Dividends.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 199631.0,
      "end_time": 202166.0,
      "text": "This represents the first time"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 202190.0,
      "end_time": 205781.0,
      "text": "that Republican leaders put forth"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 205805.0,
      "end_time": 208318.0,
      "text": "a concrete market-based climate solution."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 208342.0,
      "end_time": 209723.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 209747.0,
      "end_time": 210816.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 210840.0,
      "end_time": 213443.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 213467.0,
      "end_time": 215794.0,
      "text": "We presented our plan at the White House"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 215818.0,
      "end_time": 218520.0,
      "text": "two weeks after President Trump moved in."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 219465.0,
      "end_time": 223343.0,
      "text": "Almost every leading editorial board in the country"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 223367.0,
      "end_time": 225613.0,
      "text": "has since endorsed our plan,"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 225638.0,
      "end_time": 230323.0,
      "text": "and Fortune 100 companies from a wide range of industries"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 230347.0,
      "end_time": 232698.0,
      "text": "are now getting behind it."
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 232722.0,
      "end_time": 234683.0,
      "text": "So by now you&#39;re probably wondering,"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 234707.0,
      "end_time": 237108.0,
      "text": "what exactly is this plan?"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 237133.0,
      "end_time": 241501.0,
      "text": "Well, our carbon dividends solution is based on four pillars."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 241525.0,
      "end_time": 245435.0,
      "text": "The first is a gradually rising carbon tax."
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 245459.0,
      "end_time": 247986.0,
      "text": "Although capitalism is a wonderful system,"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 248100.0,
      "end_time": 251185.0,
      "text": "like many operating systems, it&#39;s prone to bugs,"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 251209.0,
      "end_time": 254402.0,
      "text": "which, in this case, are called \"market failures.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 254426.0,
      "end_time": 257947.0,
      "text": "By far the largest is that market prices fail to take"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 257971.0,
      "end_time": 261710.0,
      "text": "social and environmental costs into account."
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 261735.0,
      "end_time": 267750.0,
      "text": "That means every market transaction is based on incorrect information."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 267990.0,
      "end_time": 271197.0,
      "text": "This fundamental bug of capitalism, more than any other single factor,"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 271221.0,
      "end_time": 273977.0,
      "text": "is to blame for our climate predicament."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 274580.0,
      "end_time": 277890.0,
      "text": "Now in theory, this should be an easy problem to fix."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 277915.0,
      "end_time": 279281.0,
      "text": "Economists agree"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 279305.0,
      "end_time": 284930.0,
      "text": "that the best solution is to put a price on the carbon content of fossil fuels,"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 284117.0,
      "end_time": 286391.0,
      "text": "otherwise known as a carbon tax."
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 286415.0,
      "end_time": 290143.0,
      "text": "This would discourage carbon emissions"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 290167.0,
      "end_time": 292486.0,
      "text": "in every single economic transaction,"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 292511.0,
      "end_time": 294221.0,
      "text": "every day of the year."
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 294245.0,
      "end_time": 299591.0,
      "text": "However, a carbon tax by itself has proven to be unpopular"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 299615.0,
      "end_time": 301283.0,
      "text": "and a political dead end."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 301813.0,
      "end_time": 305337.0,
      "text": "The answer is to return all the money raised"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 305362.0,
      "end_time": 307654.0,
      "text": "directly to citizens,"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 307678.0,
      "end_time": 311290.0,
      "text": "in the form of equal monthly dividends."
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 311499.0,
      "end_time": 315310.0,
      "text": "This would transform an unpopular carbon tax"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 315550.0,
      "end_time": 318297.0,
      "text": "into a popular and populist solution,"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 318321.0,
      "end_time": 320145.0,
      "text": "and it would also solve"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 320169.0,
      "end_time": 323482.0,
      "text": "the underlying psychological barrier that we discussed,"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 323506.0,
      "end_time": 328183.0,
      "text": "by giving everyone a concrete benefit in the here and now."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 329127.0,
      "end_time": 331416.0,
      "text": "And these benefits would be significant."
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 331440.0,
      "end_time": 335182.0,
      "text": "Assuming a carbon tax rate that starts at 40 dollars per ton,"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 335206.0,
      "end_time": 338629.0,
      "text": "a family of four would receive 2,000 dollars per year"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 338653.0,
      "end_time": 339884.0,
      "text": "from the get-go."
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 340463.0,
      "end_time": 342706.0,
      "text": "According to the US Treasury Department,"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 343459.0,
      "end_time": 348489.0,
      "text": "the bottom 70 percent of Americans would receive more in dividends"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 348513.0,
      "end_time": 351804.0,
      "text": "than they would pay in increased energy prices."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 351828.0,
      "end_time": 358820.0,
      "text": "That means 223 million Americans would win economically"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 358845.0,
      "end_time": 360855.0,
      "text": "from solving climate change."
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 361631.0,
      "end_time": 362792.0,
      "text": "And that --"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 362817.0,
      "end_time": 363872.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 363896.0,
      "end_time": 365446.0,
      "text": "is revolutionary,"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 365470.0,
      "end_time": 369201.0,
      "text": "and could fundamentally alter climate politics."
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 370598.0,
      "end_time": 373415.0,
      "text": "But there&#39;s another revolutionary element here."
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 373439.0,
      "end_time": 376919.0,
      "text": "The amount of the dividend would grow"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 376943.0,
      "end_time": 379304.0,
      "text": "as the carbon tax rate increases."
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 379328.0,
      "end_time": 381404.0,
      "text": "The more we protect our climate,"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 381428.0,
      "end_time": 383283.0,
      "text": "the more our citizens benefit."
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 383307.0,
      "end_time": 385529.0,
      "text": "This creates a positive feedback loop,"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 385553.0,
      "end_time": 387820.0,
      "text": "which is crucial,"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 387107.0,
      "end_time": 391300.0,
      "text": "because the only way we will reach our long-term emission-reduction goals"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 391270.0,
      "end_time": 393782.0,
      "text": "is if the carbon tax rate goes up every year."
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 394799.0,
      "end_time": 398765.0,
      "text": "The third pillar of our program is eliminating regulations"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 398789.0,
      "end_time": 400328.0,
      "text": "that are no longer needed"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 400352.0,
      "end_time": 403429.0,
      "text": "once a carbon dividends plan is enacted."
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 403454.0,
      "end_time": 409883.0,
      "text": "This is a key selling point to Republicans and business leaders."
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 410919.0,
      "end_time": 412443.0,
      "text": "So why should we trade"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 412986.0,
      "end_time": 415517.0,
      "text": "climate regulations for a price on carbon?"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 415541.0,
      "end_time": 417319.0,
      "text": "Well, let me show you."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 417996.0,
      "end_time": 422424.0,
      "text": "Our plan would achieve nearly twice the emissions reductions"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 422448.0,
      "end_time": 426604.0,
      "text": "of all Obama-era climate regulations combined,"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 426628.0,
      "end_time": 430238.0,
      "text": "and nearly three times the new baseline"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 430262.0,
      "end_time": 434419.0,
      "text": "after President Trump repeals all of those regulations."
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 434443.0,
      "end_time": 438205.0,
      "text": "That assumes a carbon tax starting at 40 dollars per ton,"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 438230.0,
      "end_time": 443223.0,
      "text": "which translates into roughly an extra 36 cents per gallon of gas."
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 443882.0,
      "end_time": 446391.0,
      "text": "Our plan by itself"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 446415.0,
      "end_time": 449988.0,
      "text": "would meet the high end of America&#39;s commitment"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 450120.0,
      "end_time": 452290.0,
      "text": "under the Paris Climate Agreement,"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 452314.0,
      "end_time": 453988.0,
      "text": "and as you can see,"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 454120.0,
      "end_time": 456998.0,
      "text": "the emissions reductions would continue over time."
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 457521.0,
      "end_time": 463890.0,
      "text": "This illustrates the power of a conservative climate solution"
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 463113.0,
      "end_time": 466100.0,
      "text": "based on free markets and limited government."
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 466250.0,
      "end_time": 469203.0,
      "text": "We would end up with less regulation"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 469228.0,
      "end_time": 472320.0,
      "text": "and far less pollution at the same time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 472344.0,
      "end_time": 476328.0,
      "text": "while helping working-class Americans get ahead."
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 476352.0,
      "end_time": 479590.0,
      "text": "Doesn&#39;t that sound like something we could all support?"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 479614.0,
      "end_time": 482460.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 485723.0,
      "end_time": 490242.0,
      "text": "The fourth and final pillar of our program is a new climate domino effect,"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 490266.0,
      "end_time": 492920.0,
      "text": "based on border carbon adjustments."
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 492944.0,
      "end_time": 495470.0,
      "text": "Now that may sound complicated,"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 495710.0,
      "end_time": 496936.0,
      "text": "but it, too, is revolutionary,"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 496960.0,
      "end_time": 499820.0,
      "text": "because it provides us a whole new strategy"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 499845.0,
      "end_time": 502393.0,
      "text": "to reach a global price on carbon,"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 502417.0,
      "end_time": 504284.0,
      "text": "which is ultimately what we need."
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 504308.0,
      "end_time": 506240.0,
      "text": "Let me show you an example."
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 506264.0,
      "end_time": 509765.0,
      "text": "Suppose Country A adopts a carbon dividends plan,"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 509789.0,
      "end_time": 511236.0,
      "text": "and Country B does not."
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 511260.0,
      "end_time": 513663.0,
      "text": "Well, to level the playing field"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 513687.0,
      "end_time": 516922.0,
      "text": "and protect the competitiveness of its industries,"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 516946.0,
      "end_time": 520844.0,
      "text": "Country A would tax imports from Country B"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 520868.00000000006,
      "end_time": 522707.00000000006,
      "text": "based on their carbon content."
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 522731.0,
      "end_time": 524248.0,
      "text": "Fair enough."
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 524272.00000000006,
      "end_time": 526416.0,
      "text": "But here&#39;s where it gets really interesting,"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 526440.0,
      "end_time": 530780.0,
      "text": "because the money raised at the border would increase the dividends"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 530102.0,
      "end_time": 532356.0,
      "text": "going to the citizens of Country A."
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 532380.0,
      "end_time": 536552.0,
      "text": "Well, how long do you think it would take the public in Country B to realize"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 536576.0,
      "end_time": 538508.0,
      "text": "that that money should be going to them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 538533.0,
      "end_time": 541522.0,
      "text": "and to push for a carbon dividends plan in their own land?"
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 541546.0,
      "end_time": 543450.0,
      "text": "Add a few more countries,"
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 543690.0,
      "end_time": 546526.0,
      "text": "and we get a new climate domino effect."
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 547337.0,
      "end_time": 551626.0,
      "text": "Once one major country or region adopts carbon dividends"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 551650.0,
      "end_time": 553275.0,
      "text": "with border carbon adjustments,"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 553299.0,
      "end_time": 555757.0,
      "text": "other countries are compelled to follow suit."
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 555782.0,
      "end_time": 558694.0,
      "text": "One by one the dominoes fall."
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 558718.0,
      "end_time": 561460.0,
      "text": "And this domino effect could start anywhere."
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 561710.0,
      "end_time": 564481.0,
      "text": "My preference, strongly, is the United States,"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 564505.0,
      "end_time": 567320.0,
      "text": "but it could also start in the United Kingdom,"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 567560.0,
      "end_time": 569264.0,
      "text": "in Germany or another European country,"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 569288.0,
      "end_time": 570816.0,
      "text": "or even in China."
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 571832.0,
      "end_time": 573842.0,
      "text": "Let&#39;s take China as an example."
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 573866.0,
      "end_time": 578410.0,
      "text": "China is committed to reducing greenhouse gas emissions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 578434.0,
      "end_time": 580775.0,
      "text": "but what its leaders care even more about"
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 580799.0,
      "end_time": 585776.0,
      "text": "is transitioning their economy to consumer-led economic development."
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 585800.0,
      "end_time": 588675.0,
      "text": "Well, nothing could do more to hasten that transition"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 588700.0,
      "end_time": 591979.0,
      "text": "than giving every Chinese citizen a monthly dividend."
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 592300.0,
      "end_time": 595524.0,
      "text": "In fact, this is the only policy solution"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 595548.0,
      "end_time": 599190.0,
      "text": "that would enable China to meet its environmental and economic goals"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 599214.0,
      "end_time": 600572.0,
      "text": "at the same time."
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 600596.0,
      "end_time": 603973.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s why this is the killer app of climate policy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 603997.0,
      "end_time": 607336.0,
      "text": "because it would enable us to overcome"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 607360.0,
      "end_time": 609673.0,
      "text": "each of the barriers we discussed earlier:"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 609697.0,
      "end_time": 612781.0,
      "text": "the psychological barrier, the partisan barrier,"
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 612805.0,
      "end_time": 616265.0,
      "text": "and, as we&#39;ve just seen, the geopolitical barrier."
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 616289.0,
      "end_time": 620266.0,
      "text": "All we need is a country to lead the way."
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 620291.0,
      "end_time": 622720.0,
      "text": "And one method of finding what you&#39;re looking for"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 622744.0,
      "end_time": 624404.0,
      "text": "is to take out an ad."
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 624428.0,
      "end_time": 626407.0,
      "text": "So let&#39;s read this one together."
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 626431.0,
      "end_time": 630241.0,
      "text": "Wanted: country to pioneer carbon dividends plan."
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 630265.0,
      "end_time": 632124.0,
      "text": "Cost to country: zero."
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 632732.0,
      "end_time": 635110.0,
      "text": "Starting date: as soon as possible."
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 635350.0,
      "end_time": 638477.0,
      "text": "Advantages: most effective climate solution,"
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 638501.0,
      "end_time": 640257.0,
      "text": "popular and populist,"
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 640282.0,
      "end_time": 642124.0,
      "text": "pro-growth and pro-business,"
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 642148.0,
      "end_time": 645490.0,
      "text": "shrinks government and helps the working class."
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 647101.0,
      "end_time": 652418.0,
      "text": "Additional compensation: gratitude of current and future generations,"
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 653458.0,
      "end_time": 655626.0,
      "text": "including my daughter."
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 656310.0,
      "end_time": 657183.0,
      "text": "Thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 657207.0,
      "end_time": 664207.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 664461.0,
      "end_time": 666707.0,
      "text": "Chris Anderson: Just one question for you, Ted."
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 669221.0,
      "end_time": 670371.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m actually not sure"
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 670396.0,
      "end_time": 673272.0,
      "text": "I&#39;ve seen a conservative get a standing O at TED before that."
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 673317.0,
      "end_time": 674745.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s pretty cool."
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 675554.0,
      "end_time": 677379.0,
      "text": "The logic seems really powerful,"
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 677404.0,
      "end_time": 679473.0,
      "text": "but some people you talk to in politics"
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 679498.0,
      "end_time": 683569.0,
      "text": "say it&#39;s hard to imagine this still getting through Congress."
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 683593.0,
      "end_time": 685807.0,
      "text": "How are you feeling about momentum behind this?"
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 686132.0,
      "end_time": 689756.0,
      "text": "Ted Halstead: So I understand that many are very pessimistic"
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 689781.0,
      "end_time": 692829.0,
      "text": "about what&#39;s happening in the United States with President Trump."
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 692854.0,
      "end_time": 694432.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m less pessimistic; here&#39;s why."
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 694457.0,
      "end_time": 697462.0,
      "text": "The actions of this White House, the early actions on climate,"
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 697487.0,
      "end_time": 703650.0,
      "text": "are just the first move in a complex game of climate chess."
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 703900.0,
      "end_time": 705700.0,
      "text": "So far it&#39;s been a repeal-only strategy;"
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 705725.0,
      "end_time": 708574.0,
      "text": "the pressure is going to mount  for a replacement program,"
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 708599.0,
      "end_time": 709845.0,
      "text": "which is where we come in."
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 709869.0,
      "end_time": 713670.0,
      "text": "And there are three reasons why, which I&#39;ll go through real quickly."
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 713910.0,
      "end_time": 716303.0,
      "text": "One, the business community is fundamentally parting ways"
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 716328.0,
      "end_time": 718762.0,
      "text": "with the White House on climate change."
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 718788.0,
      "end_time": 719938.0,
      "text": "In fact, we&#39;re finding"
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 719963.0,
      "end_time": 723730.0,
      "text": "a number of Fortune 100 companies supporting our program."
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 723980.0,
      "end_time": 725295.0,
      "text": "Within two months, we&#39;re going to be announcing"
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 725321.0,
      "end_time": 728376.0,
      "text": "some really surprising names coming out in favor of this program."
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 728400.0,
      "end_time": 731531.0,
      "text": "Two, there is no issue in American politics"
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 731557.0,
      "end_time": 735366.0,
      "text": "where there&#39;s a more fundamental gap between the Republican base"
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 735391.0,
      "end_time": 738260.0,
      "text": "and the Republican leadership than climate change."
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 738500.0,
      "end_time": 742780.0,
      "text": "And three, thinking of this analogy of chess,"
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 743225.0,
      "end_time": 747454.0,
      "text": "the big decision up ahead is: Does the administration stay in Paris?"
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 747478.0,
      "end_time": 749640.0,
      "text": "Well, let&#39;s pan it out both ways."
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 749129.0,
      "end_time": 752835.0,
      "text": "If it stays in Paris, as many are pushing for in the administration,"
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 752946.0,
      "end_time": 755462.0,
      "text": "well then that begs a question: What&#39;s the plan?"
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 755565.0,
      "end_time": 756795.0,
      "text": "We have the plan."
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 757490.0,
      "end_time": 759119.0,
      "text": "But if they don&#39;t stay in Paris,"
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 759144.0,
      "end_time": 761596.0,
      "text": "the international pressure will be overwhelming."
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 761620.0,
      "end_time": 765246.0,
      "text": "Our Secretary of State will be asking other countries for NATO contributions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 765271.0,
      "end_time": 768171.0,
      "text": "and they&#39;ll be saying, \"No, give us our Paris commitment."
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 768197.0,
      "end_time": 771109.0,
      "text": "Come through on your commitments, we&#39;ll come through on ours.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 771133.0,
      "end_time": 774427.0,
      "text": "So, international, business and even the Republican base"
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 774451.0,
      "end_time": 778216.0,
      "text": "will all be calling for a Republican replacement plan."
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 778397.0,
      "end_time": 781890.0,
      "text": "And, hopefully, we&#39;ve provided one."
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 781351.0,
      "end_time": 782637.0,
      "text": "CA: Thank you so much, Ted."
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 782662.0,
      "end_time": 783812.0,
      "text": "TH: Thank you, Chris."
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 783837.0,
      "end_time": 787399.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}